    <title>work: serialize model-backed readiness before claim races</title>
    <description>
PROBLEM&#xA;`ddx work` now runs model-backed bead readiness intake and bead-lifecycle lint after selecting a ready bead but before atomically claiming it. With two workers on the same project, both workers can select the same bead, both spend model calls on intake/lint, and both can append pre-dispatch events before one loses `Store.Claim`. If intake returns `actionable_but_rewritten`, the loser can also mutate bead description/acceptance before owning the bead. Atomic `Store.Claim` still prevents duplicate implementation, but it no longer protects the expensive and stateful pre-claim phase.&#xA;&#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE&#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:686-765 calls `runtime.PreClaimIntakeHook` and handles rewrite/block outcomes before `w.Store.Claim` is attempted.&#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:768-807 calls `runtime.PreDispatchLintHook` and `appendPreDispatchLintEvent` before the claim, so concurrent workers can append duplicate lint events for the same open bead.&#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:809-823 only detects the ownership race after intake/lint have already run.&#xA;- cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_rewrite.go:39-58 loads and updates bead description/acceptance from the intake rewrite path without a prior worker claim/ownership check.&#xA;- cli/internal/bead/store.go:588-635 makes `ClaimWithOptions` the atomic ownership boundary, but `ReadyExecution` at cli/internal/bead/store.go:1352-1355 only lists candidates and does not reserve them.&#xA;&#xA;PROPOSED FIX&#xA;- Move the expensive/model-backed readiness and lint gates behind an atomic worker reservation, or add an equivalent atomic `ReserveForReadiness` lease that removes the bead from other workers while intake/lint runs.&#xA;- If the chosen design uses ordinary claim before readiness: claim first, start heartbeat, run intake and lint, then unclaim/release on retryable intake errors, park with `needs_human`/triage metadata on terminal readiness outcomes, and continue to implementation only for actionable beads.&#xA;- If the chosen design uses a separate readiness lease: make `ReadyExecution` exclude fresh readiness leases, make stale leases reclaimable, and require rewrite/lint event mutations to verify lease ownership.&#xA;- Ensure `actionable_but_rewritten` applies metadata under the same ownership/lease used by the worker, so concurrent workers cannot double-rewrite or append conflicting events.&#xA;- Preserve the existing atomic `Store.Claim` duplicate-implementation guarantee and existing `picker.claim_race` telemetry for true claim races.&#xA;&#xA;NON-SCOPE&#xA;- Changing the bead-lifecycle rubric or model prompt content.&#xA;- Removing readiness/lint checks entirely.&#xA;- Changing final implementation landing/review semantics.&#xA;&#xA;DEPS&#xA;No deps. This is a queue safety bug introduced by the current pre-claim intake ordering and can be fixed independently of the parked-bead triage work.
    </description>
    <acceptance>
1. `TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentPreClaimIntakeRunsOncePerBead` starts two workers against one ready bead with a blocking `PreClaimIntakeHook` and proves only one worker enters the model-backed intake for that bead while the other observes it as unavailable or moves on.&#xA;2. `TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentPreDispatchLintDoesNotDuplicateEvents` proves two workers cannot append duplicate `bead-quality.lint` events for the same readiness attempt before ownership is established.&#xA;3. `TestPreClaimIntakeRewriteRequiresOwnedReservation` proves `actionable_but_rewritten` cannot update description/acceptance unless the worker owns the claim/readiness lease, and concurrent losers leave the bead unchanged.&#xA;4. `TestExecuteBeadWorkerReadinessRejectReleasesOrParksClaim` covers intake error, ambiguous/needs-human, and lint-block outcomes: retryable errors release the bead or set a bounded cooldown; terminal readiness outcomes park with explicit labels/metadata; actionable beads proceed to implementation.&#xA;5. Existing `TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentWorkersDoNotDoubleExecuteSameBead` and `TestExecuteLoop_TwoWorkersBothClaimP0sBeforeP2s` still pass, preserving duplicate-implementation protection and priority ordering.&#xA;6. WIRED-IN: production `ExecuteBeadWorker.Run` uses the new claim/reservation boundary before invoking `PreClaimIntakeHook`, `applyPreClaimIntakeRewrite`, or `appendPreDispatchLintEvent`.&#xA;7. cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run &#34;TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentPreClaim|TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentPreDispatch|TestPreClaimIntakeRewriteRequiresOwnedReservation|TestExecuteBeadWorkerReadinessReject|TestExecuteBeadWorkerConcurrentWorkersDoNotDoubleExecuteSameBead|TestExecuteLoop_TwoWorkersBothClaimP0sBeforeP2s&#34; -count=1 passes.&#xA;8. cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... passes.&#xA;9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.
    </acceptance>
